<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880920-0070 </DOCNO><HL> Arco Unit Receives $301.9 Million Job From Defense Unit </HL><SO> </SO><CO> ARC EMR CUM GE MD CTC LTV </CO><IN> ARO PET </IN><G> DEF </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Arco Products Co., a unit of Atlantic Richfield Co., received a $301.9 million contract from the Defense Logistics Agency for jet fuel.    Emerson Electric Co. was awarded $48.6 million in Army contracts for helicopter and armored-vehicle parts.    Pentastar Electronics Inc. received a $30.7 million Army contract for electrical-test sets.    Cummins Engine Co. was issued a $26.2 million Army contract for diesel engines.    General Electric Co. got a $20 million Air Force contract for helicopter-modification kits.    McDonnell Douglas Corp. received a $19.3 million Army contract for helicopter transmissions.    Contel Corp. won a $16.5 million Army contract for telephone systems.    Accudyne Corp. was issued a $15.8 million Army contract for ground mines.    Engineered Air Systems Inc. won a $15 million Army contract for laundry units.    AM General Corp., a unit of LTV Corp., received a $14.8 million Army contract for heavy trucks. </TEXT></DOC>